(AI CUSTOMER SUPPORT CHATBOT - TABLE STRUCTURE AND DATA FLOW) Tj
T*
(===========================================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. PURPOSE) Tj
T*
(----------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document explains the database table structure, Redis session structure, data movement) Tj
T*
(across tables, and business logic used in the AI customer support chatbot project.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project handles an e-commerce order complaint flow:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. User starts a complaint.) Tj
T*
(2. Bot asks for order ID.) Tj
T*
(3. Backend validates the order.) Tj
T*
(4. Backend creates a ticket.) Tj
T*
(5. User selects order item\(s\).) Tj
T*
(6. Backend stores selected ticket items.) Tj
T*
(7. User provides the issue type.) Tj
T*
(8. Backend checks duplicates.) Tj
T*
(9. Backend calculates refund.) Tj
T*
(10. Backend escalates or resolves the ticket.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The application is intentionally monolithic and enterprise-style:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- WebSocket controller only receives and returns messages.) Tj
T*
(- ChatService owns the conversation state machine.) Tj
T*
(- Domain services handle focused operations.) Tj
T*
(- PostgreSQL stores permanent data.) Tj
T*
(- Redis stores temporary conversation session state.) Tj
T*
(- AI gives structured signals only; backend makes final decisions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. MAIN STORAGE TYPES) Tj
T*
(---------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PostgreSQL) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PostgreSQL stores permanent data:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Orders) Tj
T*
(- Order items) Tj
T*
(- Tickets) Tj
T*
(- Ticket items) Tj
T*
(- Chat messages) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These records should remain even after Redis expires or the application restarts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Redis) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Redis stores temporary conversation state:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Current user state) Tj
T*
(- Current ticket ID) Tj
T*
(- Selected item IDs) Tj
T*
(- Retry count) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Redis key format:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```text) Tj
T*
(session:{userId}) Tj
T*
(Page 1) Tj
