(`tickets.order_id` is stored as a string instead of a JPA relation. This keeps the complaint) Tj
T*
(domain simple and avoids accidental order updates through ticket logic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Status meaning:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Status | Meaning |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| OPEN | Complaint is currently active |) Tj
T*
(| RESOLVED | Refund was initiated and ticket is complete |) Tj
T*
(| ESCALATED | Ticket needs human support |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(State meaning:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| State | Meaning |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| START | New conversation |) Tj
T*
(| ASK_ORDER_ID | Bot is waiting for the order ID |) Tj
T*
(| SELECT_ITEMS | Bot is waiting for item selection |) Tj
T*
(| ASK_ISSUE | Bot is waiting for issue type |) Tj
T*
(| PROCESS_REFUND | Backend is ready to calculate refund and decide final status |) Tj
T*
(| RESOLVED | Ticket was resolved |) Tj
T*
(| ESCALATED | Ticket was escalated |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
