T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(13. TRANSACTION HANDLING) Tj
T*
(------------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(`ChatServiceImpl.handleMessage\(\)` is annotated with:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```java) Tj
T*
(@Transactional) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Meaning:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- The DB operations inside one chat message are part of one transaction.) Tj
T*
(- If a runtime error happens during ticket/item/message persistence, the transaction can roll) Tj
T*
(  back.) Tj
T*
(- Redis session write happens at the end, after response creation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Note:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Redis is not part of the relational DB transaction. This is acceptable because PostgreSQL is the) Tj
T*
(permanent truth and Redis can be recovered from tickets.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(14. IMPORTANT BUSINESS RULES) Tj
T*
(----------------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. AI must not calculate refund.) Tj
T*
(2. AI must not directly update ticket status.) Tj
T*
(3. AI must not write to the database.) Tj
T*
(4. Backend validates order ownership before ticket creation.) Tj
T*
(5. Backend stores selected complaint items in `ticket_items`.) Tj
T*
(6. Duplicate complaint detection happens before final resolution.) Tj
T*
(7. High refund amount escalates.) Tj
T*
(8. Angry/frustrated users can be escalated through AI signal.) Tj
T*
(9. Out-of-scope messages are rejected.) Tj
T*
(10. Redis session expiry should not lose active tickets.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(15. SUGGESTED FUTURE IMPROVEMENTS) Tj
T*
(---------------------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Add explicit foreign key from `tickets.order_id` to `customer_orders.order_id`.) Tj
T*
(2. Add indexes:) Tj
T*
(   - `tickets\(user_id, status, updated_at\)`) Tj
T*
(   - `tickets\(user_id, order_id, issue_type\)`) Tj
T*
(   - `chat_messages\(user_id, timestamp\)`) Tj
T*
(   - `ticket_items\(ticket_id\)`) Tj
T*
(3. Store AI signal audit in a separate table if needed:) Tj
T*
(   - `ai_analysis_logs`) Tj
T*
(4. Add a REST admin endpoint for loading orders.) Tj
T*
(5. Add integration tests for duplicate complaint and escalation flows.) Tj
T*
(6. Add a support-agent assignment table for escalated tickets.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Page 18) Tj
ET
endstream
